{
  "texts": [
    "For the evaluation data set, we take all the test set output from Task-1 'clinical case' reports since this is the only task with full sentences.",
    "For the other two tasks on term and ontology level translation, MT engines can perform relatively good outcomes even without an effective encoder-decoder neural model, e.g.",
    "via a well prepared bilingual dictionary.",
    "We prepared 100 strings for each set and delivered all the sets to 5 professional evaluators.",
    "6 The tasks consisted of strings of medical cases going in order one by one, so the context of each case was clear to the evaluator."
  ]
}